  "text": "The chain from Deployment spec change to Pod creation: (1) DeploymentController.syncDeployment (deployment_controller.go) is the main reconcile entry point \u2014 it calls dc.sync(), dc.rolloutRolling(), or dc.rolloutRecreate() depending on strategy. (2) sync.go contains sync() which calls getNewReplicaSet() to create/find the ReplicaSet, and scale() to adjust replica counts. (3) ReplicaSetController.syncReplicaSet (replica_set.go) reconciles ReplicaSets \u2014 it calls manageReplicas() which calls rsc.podControl.CreatePods() to create pods. (4) CreatePods in controller_utils.go (RealPodControl) constructs the Pod object and calls the API. (5) The API server handles pod creation via the generic store.Create() in store.go, with pod-specific validation/defaulting in pod/strategy.go (PrepareForCreate), and pod storage registration in pod/storage/storage.go.",
